                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="47314" author="joshua" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2012 15:21:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Deleted RPMs due to IT-176 (stop distributing lustre-diagnostics, as we did not have the correct license).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47110" author="rhenwood" created="Tue, 30 Oct 2012 15:07:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;lustre-diagnostics is not supported.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45595" author="rhenwood" created="Wed, 26 Sep 2012 15:32:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated RPMs are attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45465" author="rhenwood" created="Mon, 24 Sep 2012 17:09:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems that it is not possible to disable download of attachments without modifying the code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Downloading attachments is necessary as the browser needs to maintain common domain security principle. Currently, Jira insists on downloading an attachment, so the browser thinks the attached xml is actually on localhost - and because of common domain security, it won&apos;t apply the xsl.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have found this page that proposed code to alter this behaviour:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://confluence.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=215484007&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://confluence.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=215484007&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="27773" author="rhenwood" created="Thu, 2 Feb 2012 11:39:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve had a good go at trying to get automated posting to Jira. I have not succeeded. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve looked through some of the readily available resources to get this going, including:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRACOM/Automating+JIRA+operations+via+wget&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRACOM/Automating+JIRA+operations+via+wget&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, there is evidence that it is not possible with the Jira version that we&apos;re running:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-23279&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-23279&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On principal, I&apos;m believe that curl/wget should be able to post - but having spent a couple of sessions on this issue, I am going to wait for the Jira update - that is apparently due in Q1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
